LORE kowloon-syndic
FLAGS KOWLOON MERCHANT
Harbor Syndics in blue sashes audit every cargo manifest at the Tide Gate;
their blue lanterns line the harbor channel for night navigation
Operations are intertwined with smuggling networks; the Jade Eels syndicate
is believed to hold a Syndic seat; enforcement is selective by design
Jade Magistracy can override market pricing during emergency declarations;
invoke the jade seal requirement (40 lbs, requires two magistrates) as
assurance that emergencies are not declared casually
Gold lacquer on a doorframe = owner has posted bond against fraud with the
Magistracy; jade ribbon on a merchant stall = weights audited this season
Violet-marked night markets operate outside guild oversight; prices are
negotiable; provenance documentation is sparse; buyer's risk
Coppersalt Bay weather changes fast; mountain thermals, not the sky;
a pilot who reads the sky is behind the storm by an hour
~
